This is our favorite neighborhood bar in East Lakeview.  We live in Lakeview part time and stop in every time we are in the area.  The food is consistent (taste and presentation), the outdoor seating space allows for great people watching, and staff is attentive.  Great place to stop on your way to a Cubs game.

The Wrigley Burger here is one of the best burgers on the scene. Super low-key place to grab a bite and have some drinks. The staff is super friendly. They also have a  wildly extensive whiskey selection.

AVOID. Honestly the worst experience I have ever had at a bar. To order food and drinks for a party of 4 where the majority of the food is fried besides one sandwich and to wait over an hour, have a complete other couple come in and order later than us, be served, finish their meals, and leave before even getting our food and wait another 15 minutes is beyond horrible. Not to mention that they didn't even apologize or acknowledge the long wait until we mentioned it (several times), instead trying to get us to drink more. I have been to this place before for food and drinks while it was busy, unlike tonight, and never waited this long. I honestly got so irritated that I lost my appetite and didn't touch my food when it arrived. I just moved into the neighborhood and will not be coming back. Plenty of other bars with great food, drinks, and better customer service. Great job losing a new local.

Angie. My server was Angie. I give 1 star only because of her. I have been coming to this place for 2 years but since then a lot of things have changed. Most importantly the serving staff. They are certainly either racist or outright uninterested in serving you. I was shown the check after each of my 4 consecutive orders, and I never asked for check once. Which clearly meant that Angie wanted my party to leave. And this is when we were the only ones in pub at 9pm on a Friday night. And then she started serving us drinks in plastic cups. Another sign of disrespect, blatantly saying that we should leave. I mean, I get it that we don't look like her, but this is just insulting. Never returning to this place again.

A typical Irish Bar. Ordered an interesting burger with candied bacon and peanut butter and goat cheese, which didn't blow my mind but was good. Oddly stingy on the French Fries which surprised the hell out of me! Management: Never skimp on the fries!  Also, I wound up getting peanut butter all over the damn place.  Reasonable beer selection, nice environment, and great service, though!

A great neighborhood bar with excellent beer selection (the 3 Floyds rotating tap is always a great choice). Good food, too. Trivia night at 8:30 on Wednesdays is always a good time, but be sure to come early for a table. I do wish they had specials for trivia... most bars will have all-day specials for trivia night.

Upscale pub food at a reasonable price. Fast, helpful service. Good beer selection. And the best cheese curds I've found in Chicago so far. I'm really happy I found this gem in my neighborhood. I'll definitely be back!

Eat here!  F.O'Mahony's is a great casual bar with excellent beer selection (including a rotating 3 Floyd's draft). The food features elevated classics: burgers, sandwiches, etc. with complex flavors and top quality.  Skip the alternatives in Wrigleyville and eat here instead!
A divey hole in the wall with good food and a fun clientele.  TV's adorn the walls and Tues is burger special night.

Fantastic food in a friendly environment. The atmosphere of the bar is lively, the staff are attentive and friendly. The wings are amazing, crispy and flavorful. One of the best wings I've had around the neighborhood.  The burger was good, but the wings definitely stood out
Mahoney's never disappoints. Great neighborhood option with friendly service and above par food and drinks.
Great fun place with excellent staff
Good food,  great service here. David was perfect! Highly recommend this place!

Friendly neighborhood bar. Staff is very attentive and just nice people.  The food is what you would expect - not exceptional, but fairly.  Tuesday night beer and burger special is my favorite.  Rarely miss it.

Drink selection, bar atmosphere, etc. is good. Nice local neighborhood bar. I would've given them 4 stars aside from the fact that they are not Vegetarian/Vegan/Gluten free friendly. When I politely called this to the wait staff's attention (a specific issue), she was understanding, however, the management there has no empathy for alternative diets. Many people have brought this to the wait staff's attention but management seems to not care about improving their experience for these customers and only about saving nickels and times for the production cost of an alternative.

Good local neighborhood corner bar.  Always has the best games on the many tvs.  Good food with a good beer & drink selection.  Mikey the owner is there often greeting people.  Very much a Cheers type atmosphere. Also a good Sunday brunch.
Excellent weekend brunch!

So. Damn. Delicious. Monday and Tuesday night food specials are what I go for. I don't even drink alcohol, so you know the food is good! Monday night 50 cent perfectly cooked wings with the best tasting buffalo, bbq or mixed sauce ever or Tuesday night $5 Angus burgers WITH fries or tots. And the tvs are perfectly placed so no matter where you're sitting you don't have to strain. According to friends their drink specials are super good too, but if you don't drink alcohol they got you as well. You can tell how well a bar keeps up it's hoses and cleanliness by how good the lemonade tastes.

Came here when trivia at the first bar we were at was cancelled.  The crowd and trivia were great, and there were some decent beer specials, but nothing crazy.  I didn't try to the food, because we'd already eaten, but the vibe of the bar was pretty good.
Good but not great, this place is a fun neighborhood bar.  Away Cubs games are print the best times to visit.

I don't usually write reviews unless it's worth it. The atmosphere is a 3 star. It's loud. You come in. You sit. But when the service begins, and you take a first bite of your food! Angles come from heaven and feed you! AMAZING! The Chef and Servers are the reason of my 5 stars. $25 bottomless mimosas and amazing food. Definitely come back. Best Brunch in Chicago!

This place is a great place that's low key to hang with the locals. The owner cares about what his patrons think about the place and is involved. The food is awesome (burger with fried egg and buffalo chicken wrap and cheese curds). I may be disowned by saying that the cheese curds here were better than those in Wisconsin, but...

Small neighborhood gastropub.  Bottomless mimosa brunch is decent value at 25, western omelette was very meaty and good.  Breakfast potatoes were good.  Staff was friendly. I might come back again if I'm in the area.
Good food, service is a little slow though. Service is nice.

I was apprehensive based on some of the negative reviews for this place but we gave it a shot anyhow. Glad we did.  It wasn't very crowded for an early dinner on a Friday (5:30PM) and service was decent (quite friendly, not fast but not too slow).  The burgers are pretty good and the meat of the fish chips was nice, but the breading on the fish 'n' chips was a little soft – not like 'soggy,' just not as crisp as we've had at other places. Drink selection was good.  We'll almost certainly be back here in the future.

Great atmosphere and friendly staff. Sundays are my favorite for the $25 brunch and mimosas. It can get pretty busy, so the earlier you make it, the better. Ultimately, it's good food, good vibes, good time.
Love love love this place!!! Best neighborhood bar ever. The staff is amazing!
Good specials through the week.  Bartenders are nice and the music is good.  Cool place!
Nice bar in East Lakeview set away from the craziness of Wrigleyville and Boystown. They've got great deals throughout the week. The food and drinks are great!
F.O.'s is a great place to go.  It's a local joint where everyone is friendly and the food and beer is awesome! If you are ever in the area you should be able stop in at the bar.

The atmosphere is a great local neighborhood bar. Abby and Sam are amazing bartenders.
